      "writtenOn": "2016-08-04T22:06:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "First, I\u0027m not sure what using std::string is buying us here, since we are already forced into the C string world by eglQueryString.  So I don\u0027t see what was wrong with the old code here.\n\nIf you do use std::string, I\u0027d always recommending doing the declaration/initialization together when possible, to eliminate code regions where the variable is not initialized to a meaningful value.  So this could have the declaration, and str could be the argument to the constructor, rather than an assignment.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 187,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 187,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "fc7b89a1c31468cffb7a8642a16888cd68b7c2d7",
